verbose_text: On the other hand, CD56 dim NK cells are CD16 high and express KIRs and/or CD94 / NKG2A; they predominate in PB (about 90% of PB NK cells); they show high baseline levels of perforin and cytotoxicity against tumor / virus infected target cells; and they also produce various cytokines in response to direct target cell interactions (Scoville et al.).
